features: 2 Modes - Converts to booster: Forward-facing harness with belt-positioning booster supports children 22-110 pounds. The height recommendation of a child in harnessed booster is 28-50 inches and in the seat belt booster mode, it is 44-57 inches
5-Point Harness with 50 pounds. Limit: Holds child's body safely and securely in the car seat
Upfront Harness Adjust: Central, front access to the harness adjuster provides an easy way to adjust child's harness for an accurate, snug fit
Shoulder Belt Guide: Automatically positions the vehicle belt in the proper position for your child
Dual Cup Holders: 2 built-in cup holders keep drinks and snacks within reach - allows driver to stay focused on the road
body.description: The Evenﬂo Maestro offers two modes of forward-facing use. Accommodating children 22-110 lbs, stage one has a 5-point harness for children at least 2 years old, and stage two allows you to use the vehicle belt as a high back booster for children at least 4 years old. The up-front harness adjustment is centralized, making it easy to properly tighten the harness. As they grow, the shoulder belt guide assists in positioning the vehicle's belt across your child's shoulder to provide optimal safety. Children appreciate the dual integrated cup holders to keep their snacks and drinks secure. The removable, machine-washable seat pad allows for easy cleanup of any messes. The Maestro is designed, engineered, tested and assembled in the United States. Evenﬂo car seats have been tested above and beyond industry standards and undergo our rigorous side impact and dynamic rollover tests. Additionally, all car seats include live video installation support, giving you the tools and conﬁdence to securely and correctly install your car seat.

productInformation.name: Care instructions
productInformation.value: ‎DO NOT lubricate or immerse in water any part of this child restraint, unless rinsing is permitted plastic and metal parts may be wiped clean with mild soap and water and dried with a soft cloth. The harness can be wiped clean with mild soap and water. Allow harness to air dry. Machine wash the seat pad separately in cold water, delicate cycle. Tumble dry 10 to 15 minutes on low heat.

reviews.reviewText: Great car seat, my toddler loves it. She has a 'big girl' seat now! Super easy to install. I got the purple one, and its a beautiful purple color. Love it, would buy again!

reviews.reviewText: Boght this to replace a baby seat fot my daughter who turned 4. We had a baby car seat and she our grew it.My daughter is tall for her age and needed a more upright seat but by law still needed to be in a car seat!This seat is perfect. Shes not leaned way back but sitting more upright. Also the straps on the other car seat were tight and I could hardly link them together.This seat will accommodate a larger child easily! We are 100% satisfied!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 24, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This is a great car seat. Not heavy and fits my 3 year old son. Very comfortable for him.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love it!! Easy to assemble and install! CUP HOLDERS screw on!
reviews.reviewText: I chose this seat due to its simple design and that it will convert as my child grows. I also liked the color choices (we got the “Whitney”).I found it to be easy to assemble and the straps were pretty easy to adjust as well.Not sure why so many customers are complaining about the cup holders falling off other than the instructions on here only seem to mention they “snap on”)…the manual that’s included with the seat clearly states to snap them in place then turn over and insert screws (included!) and screw them in place with a phillips head screw driver being careful not to over tighten. Easy!Installation was simple for me as well.Photos included show seat installed in a Hyundai Sonata. Child is 3 years old 38lbs , 37.75in tall.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars good value but cupholders fall off; cramp entry
reviews.reviewText: The seat is sturdy but light - get someone very strong to tighten the seat belt that holds it in. Buckles are stiff and hard to operate but safe. Cupholders really get in the way when you place the child in the seat - we have just left them off. All in all it's fine for occasional use; would buy again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Got this to have something that fits better in my 3rd row of my Yukon. My 5 year old was cramped in her old seat and was touching the back of the seat. She now is not touching the seat and is more comfortable. The only thing o dislike is the harness doesn’t extend very far out and can be tight! So you may have to just use the seatbelt option which I don’t want to do just yet!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: i seen some bad reviews about the cup holders, but the seat comes with two screws to screw them in, super easy! it’s light weight, love the color, my daughter loves it! and the only con i have is it was delivered in the pouring rain while i was at work and the box was so wet the seat was soaked and it is a pain in the butt to get the cover off! and put back on! but other than that i love it 10/10

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My daughter bought this for her car so I got the same one for me just a different color. I love it and my granddaughter loves it! The cup holders are great, just be sure to screw them in. My husband didn’t and they kept coming off I insisted the product was defective until my daughter said did y’all screw them in because I don’t have no problem with mine!!! #GrandparentLife

First I wasn't looking to buy a new carseat but when life hands you a car accident, you need a new car seat haha,And I absolutely love this one!First off I live the cup holders, they're deep enough that my daughter's juice boxes or bottles don't fall out and having a second one really helps because she has a spot for snacks or toys as well.Secondly, it is easy to install and as far as I can tell it is comfortable, I haven't had any complaints for my daughter so victory 😁The harness is easy to use and easy to tighten and loosen so for me that is a plus.I am really happy I came across this seat and purchased it, at first I was going by reviews and it was reasonably priced so I thought if I have to I'll go with this one, I like the look and style and after using it for over two months now I am happy to give it a good review and definitely am happy with my purchase.
